## Anti-Pattern Detection Rules

### RULE 1: Authentication Failures — CWE-287

**Priority Score: 22 | 75.8% of devs wrongly trust AI auth code**

**BAD — Weak password handling:**
```
hash = md5(password)                          // Weak hash
hash = sha256(password)                       // No salt, fast hash
IF user.password == plaintext_password:        // Plaintext comparison
```

**GOOD — Secure password handling:**
```
hash = bcrypt.hash(password, cost=12)          // Adaptive, salted
hash = argon2id.hash(password, memory=65536)   // Memory-hard
IF bcrypt.verify(password, user.password_hash): // Constant-time compare
```

**Also check for:**
- Password reset tokens that are predictable or don't expire
- Missing brute-force protection (no rate limiting or account lockout)
- Credential stuffing vectors (no CAPTCHA, no device fingerprinting)
- Password strength validation happening client-side only

---

### RULE 2: Insecure JWT Implementation — CWE-347

**BAD — Weak JWT:**
```
token = jwt.sign(payload, "my-secret", algorithm="HS256")   // Weak secret
payload = jwt.decode(token)                                   // No verification
payload = jwt.decode(token, algorithms=["HS256", "none"])     // Allows alg:none
token = jwt.sign({user: entireUserObject}, secret)            // PII in payload
```

**GOOD — Secure JWT:**
```
secret = environment.get("JWT_SECRET")
IF secret IS NULL OR secret.length < 32: THROW Error("Weak JWT secret")

token = jwt.sign(
    {sub: userId, role: user.role, exp: now + 3600, iat: now},
    secret, algorithm="HS256"
)
payload = jwt.verify(token, secret, algorithms=["HS256"])  // Strict verify
```

**Also check for:**
- No expiration or excessively long TTL (>24h for access tokens)
- Sensitive data in JWT payload (JWTs are base64, not encrypted)
- Missing refresh token rotation (allows token replay)
- JWT stored in localStorage (accessible to XSS — use httpOnly cookies)

