## Rules

- Every endpoint needs both authentication AND authorization. Missing either is a finding.
- IDOR is the most common access control failure. Any resource by ID without ownership check is a finding.
- JWTs are not encrypted. Sensitive data in a JWT payload is always a finding.
- Client-side auth checks are not security controls. Must be enforced server-side.
